            <div class='article hentry'>
              <!-- %h3.entry-title{:rel => 'bookmark'}= link_to_page(@page) -->
              <h3 class='entry-title'><a href="/2008/04/03/spec-timing">Spec Timing</a></h3>
              <div class='entry-content'>
                <p>As an update to a <a href="http://blog.tracefunc.com/2007/01/23/test-timing">previous article</a>,</p>
                
                <pre><code>if $specs_timed.nil? &amp;&amp; ENV.has_key?('SLOW')&#x000A;  $specs_timed = true&#x000A;  $timings = []&#x000A;&#x000A;  Spec::Example::ExampleGroup.prepend_before do&#x000A;    @start = Time.now&#x000A;  end&#x000A;  Spec::Example::ExampleGroup.append_after do&#x000A;    elapsed = Time.now - @start&#x000A;    if elapsed &gt; ENV['SLOW'].to_f&#x000A;      $timings &lt;&lt; [elapsed, "#{self.class.description} #{description}"]&#x000A;    end&#x000A;  end&#x000A;&#x000A;  at_exit do&#x000A;    puts "\nSlow Specs:"&#x000A;    $timings.sort{|a,b| a.first &lt;=&gt; b.first}.each do |time, name|&#x000A;      puts " %7.4f #{name}" % time&#x000A;    end&#x000A;    puts "  None!" if $timings.empty?&#x000A;  end&#x000A;end&#x000A;</code></pre>
                
                <p>Then, simply run</p>
                
                <pre><code>rake SLOW=0.1&#x000A;</code></pre>
                
                <p>Two gotchas if you're using Rails though: instead of hooking S::E::ExampleGroup, you'll need to hook Spec::Rails::Example::RailsExampleGroup.  Second, if you have any spec failures the timings don't seem to get output, since spec/rails aborts execution after failing.</p>
              </div>
              <div class='footer'>
